         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">9/5/88 ¶  ¶ It does not seem to me, dear Mr Macdonald, that we here could approach either the R.G.S. of London or the Imperial Government on Mr Bevan's behalf ¶  ¶ directly ¶ , as he was ¶  ¶ not ¶  ¶...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">88.05.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alexander Macdonald</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A38 Royal Geographical Society of Australasia (Vic. Branch) papers, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9/5/88</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It does not seem to me, dear Mr Macdonald, that we here could approach either the R.G.S. of London or the Imperial Government on Mr Bevan's behalf<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">directly</hi>
               </seg>, as he was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">our</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>emissury.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I cannot see how a recommendation, that his companions should or ought to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">share</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in any reward, could be rendering the reward useless to him, as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">he</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>would get the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">main-portion</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of it.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See T. Bevan to M, 4 May 1888, and notes thereto.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Poor Hartmann, Hunstein, Denton and many others never received anything for such discoveries, as they made by their private means and sacrificed their lives.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Carl Hartmann, Carl Hunstein, William Denton. See, respectively, M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Gardeners' chronicle</seg>, December 1887 (in this edition as 87-12-00h); M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 21 July 1891 and notes thereto; W. Armit to M, 20 July 1888.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Of course we are anxious to see Mr Bevan rewarded, but we can<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>single him out individually and overlook every one else; nor can we support a specified claim from here, as the extent of reward should be fixed<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>fixed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">above</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recommended<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">deleted</seg>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the Governor of New Guinea and the Home Government. Dr W. Macgregor is sure to be consulted anyhow by the Secr. of State for the Colonies on such a subject. In accordance with the wish of the Council I wrote a letter of felicitation to H Exc Dr M'Gregor,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to W. MacGregor, 7 May 1888<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 88-05-07a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also an unofficial letter to Sir Edw Strickland,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>asking him to favor us in the Bevan<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>case with fuller information. Copies of both letters are in my copying book here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Can you still kindly supply one or two copies of new publication.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Not identified. See M to A. Macdonald, 7 May 1888.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall make good use of them.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
